title: West Reno reopens 5 hours ago
content: Oklahoma City, Oklahoma —   Update:    Oklahoma City Police and Fire Crews have reopened W Reno Ave between N Morgan and Council. The roadway was shut down for about two and a half hours on Saturday due to a gas line being cut. Once fire crews got on the scene in the 8200 block of W Reno they found they were dealing with a medium sized pressurized gas line. It took OG&E while to get on scene and get the main shut down.    Work crews will be on scene until repairs are completed.
